Q: Variable &quot;formUser&quot; does not exist. So it does exist ! Problem communicating between files? A: <p>In controller you are passing variables to Twig</p>
<pre class="lang-php prettyprint-override"><code>return $this-&gt;render('pages/signalement/index.html.twig', [
    'form' =&gt; $formUser,
]);
</code></pre>
<p>here you rename your <code>formUser</code> to <code>form</code>.</p>
<p>So either use <code>{% include 'pages/user/_csv.html.twig' with {form: form} only %}</code></p>
<p>Or pass <code>formUser</code> initially <code>return $this-&gt;render(.., ['formUser' =&gt; $formUser])</code></p>
<hr />
<p>This code will need to be adjusted. As I understand you try to check if variable exists and then start form, so use same name:</p>
<pre><code>{% if form is defined %}
{{ form_start(form)}}
{{ form_end(form)}}
{% endif %}
</code></pre>
